## Navigation

- **Progress ledger (hybrid):** submodule **`PROGRESS.md`** files plus meta **`task/sv0-toolchain-progress.md`** — see **`.cursor/commands/continue-development.md`** (**## Progress ledger**).
- **Design questions:** **`34-user-prompts-design-only.mdc`** includes the built-in **ask-questions discipline** (one question at a time; no dependent commits on unsettled semantics). You do **not** need to paste **`/ask-questions`** for that behavior.
- **Milestone-driven development:** **`37-llm-milestone-driven-workflow.mdc`** + **`./scripts/sv0 milestone-orient`** + **`task/milestone-orientation.json`** — orient before large slices; do not equate CI green with milestone closure without the owning **`task/*.Rmd`**.
- Start from **`task/sv0-toolchain-roadmap-full.Rmd`** for **which milestone owns** each slice and the **0–3 snapshot** vs later milestones (**4–6**, cross-cutting).
- For slash commands or prompts that ask to **thoroughly execute** that roadmap file (companion verify script, validation commands, what “done” means), use **`35-sv0-roadmap-full-execution.mdc`**.
- When work is **too large to execute as one step**, decompose it in **`task/*.Rmd`** and cross-link inventories — **`36-large-task-decomposition.mdc`**.
- For **bootstrap compiler completion through self-hosting (design milestone 3)**, the live bar and sequencing live in **`task/sv0-toolchain-milestone-3-self-host.Rmd`** and **`task/sv0-toolchain-milestone-3-checklist.Rmd`** (included there). **Do not** treat documentation-only work as closing **M3**.
- **Lowering table lookups** in **`sml/ir/lowering.sml`** (e.g. **`enumTag`**, **`structFields`**, **`resolveFnCallee`**, **`resolveEnumCtorPath`**, **`splitQName`**) have **harness** seeds under **`sv0c/lib/`** (**`lower_enum_tag_core`**, **`lower_struct_fields_core`**, **`lower_resolve_fn_callee_core`**, **`lower_resolve_enum_ctor_path_core`**, **`lower_split_qname_core`**) that model hit/miss vs SML **`raise`** (or pair fallbacks) or bounded string stand-ins — not full IR types yet.

## Semantics and examples

- **Normative language and bytecode** behavior: **`sv0doc/`** first; vision HTML explains intent but does not override the spec (**`20-spec-first-language-semantics.mdc`**, **`25-sv0-design-invariants-vision.mdc`**).
- **Contracts:** clause authority and change order in **`26-sv0-contracts-clauses.mdc`**.
- **Learn tutorials vs bootstrap seeds:** **`27-examples-libraries-boundary.mdc`** — educational trees are not **`sv0c/lib/`** unless a task explicitly promotes them.

## Git and integration

- Submodule history and meta-repo pointer bumps: **`29-submodule-git-visibility.mdc`**.
- **Self-host pilot CI** vs **SML retirement**: **`28-sml-retirement-and-self-host-bar.mdc`**.

## MCP / graph

- After material edits to **`task/*.Rmd`** milestones or normative **`sv0doc/`** layout, refresh the dev graph per **`task/sv0-mcp-milestone-0.Rmd`** (submodule **`sv0-mcp`**, or **sv0-graph** **`sync_graph`**). Cursor-only or rule-only edits usually **do not** require a sync.

## Validation honesty

- **Default tiering** (same table as **`.cursor/commands/continue-development.md`** and **`thoroughly-execute-document.md`** → **Fast validation loop**): **`task/*.Rmd`**-only edits → **`./scripts/sv0 test-guards`**; one **`sv0c/`** bootstrap **`.sv0`** → **`./scripts/sv0 vm-compile <rel>`** / **`emit-c <rel>`** (`<rel>` relative to **`sv0c/`**); bootstrap lists, goldens, **`sml/`**, or cross-cutting integration → **`test-guards`** then **`./scripts/sv0 test`** before merge or “done.”
- Self-host inner loop: **`SV0_SKIP_SELF_HOST_COMPILER_DIFF=1`** (see **`sv0c/doc/self-host-sv0-loop.md`**); do not claim semantic closure with it still set.
- After pushing the meta-repo, check **GitHub Actions** with **`gh run list`** / **`gh run watch`** and name the run you used in your report (**`40-validation-and-proof.mdc`**).
- Broader CI locally: **`./scripts/sv0 test`** / **`make ci-all`** when behavior or multi-submodule integration changed.

## User prompts

- When a slash command asks you to question the user, **limit prompts to design-level or high-impact decisions**; routine execution should not stall on the user (**`34-user-prompts-design-only.mdc`**).
